OL,3,CNigel Farage demands Reform be allowed
OL,4,Cto nominate peers to the House of Lords
OL,6,FIn what ministers referred to as a
OL,7,F"first step" in wider Lord's reform,
OL,8,FLabour introduced a bill currently
OL,9,Fmaking its way through parliament
OL,10,Fwhich would remove the right to sit in
OL,11,Fthe House of Lords from the nearly 90
OL,12,Fremaining hereditary peers.
OL,14,FThey have also proposed changes to the
OL,15,Fapointments process to improve
OL,16,Fregional representation, a mandatory
OL,17,Fretirement age and a participation
OL,18,Frequirement - the latter a reference
OL,19,Fto the famously low attendance rate of
OL,20,Fsome peers.
